headline: TransDigm (TDG): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q3 Earnings?
summary: Over the past six months, TransDigm’s shares (currently trading at $1,433) have posted a disappointing 8.8% loss, well below the S&P 500’s 7.7% gain. This might have investors contemplating their next move.
